- Highly effective treatments: interventions with an effectiveness greater than 0.7;
- Basic profiles: encompass case ID, date, sex, ethnicity, vaccination status, and underlying conditions;
- The year 2021: between January 1, 2021, and December 31, 2021.

- Beacon lights: metaphorically refers to interventions; 
- Storm: refers to the number of new cases;
- The period before an intervention (beacon light is on) is when there is no match in the case-intervention table; 
- The period after an intervention is when there is a match in the case-intervention table;
- The intensity of the storm is represented by the number of daily new cases.

